Cut chicken into 3/4-inch cubes; toss chicken evenly with curry powder. Heat oil in large skillet; add chicken. Cook and stir over medium-high heat 3 minutes. Add undrained tomatoes, beans, carrots and crushed red pepper. Bring to boil; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes. Serve over rice and sprinkle with 1/4 cup peanuts or toasted coconut, if desired.